==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|la|longaevitās}}, from {{suffix|la|longaevus|-itas|alt2=-itās|gloss1=ancient, aged|nocat=1}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/lɒŋˈdʒɛ.vɪ.ti/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|longevities}}

# The quality of being [[long-lasting]], especially of [[life]]
#: ''Grandfather had incredible '''longevity''' &mdash; he lived to be 105 years old!''

====Related terms====
